        "timestamp": "2020-05-19 21:08:11.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nJohn and Ravi,\n  Per request, did a deep dive.  As noted, the user created a test case where he put in a string representation of dropping the leading zero.\n\n  The code I did on the other side (from bytes) will ALWAYS have a leading zero, because all Bytes are 2 hexes (AF, 0xAF).  A 0xF is only 4 bits, not a byte.\n\n  I did change the code to accept add number of Hexes, for library consistency sake, but since we always generate these Hexes from the sister function, and every Byte has 2 Hexes, there should be no problem.\n\n  It is, however, used in \"Cred\", so if you want, you can go through your DB and check to see if there are any String Representations with Odd number of characters.  I think you won't find any, but feel free to check.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "de2c9c2dc8c47f1e4f941d860276bc8b8fecaeb7",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3289,
          "name": "Jonathan Gathman",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jgonap@stl.gathman.org",
          "username": "instrumental"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-05-19 21:15:18.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nCorrection.  NOT used in CRED, used in AAFToken. However, AAFToken utilizes Cred DB.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
